modules.description: Parses command-line arguments directly without requiring a prior specification, using an imperative style. Processes raw strings and constructs a internal representation to generate help messages. Enables quick integration of command-line interfaces with minimal setup.

This module enables parsing of command-line inputs, including handling repeated values, boolean flags, enum options, and subcommands, while generating structured help documentation. It operates on configurations and data types such as strings, integers, floats, custom types, and enumerated values, supporting error detection and customizable parsing logic. Use cases include building robust CLI tools with dynamic option handling, validation, and user-friendly output generation.
